article.description:
Sonny Troutman matched his career high with
28 points Saturday night, leading Ohio to a 64-52 victory over
Samford.
article.headline: Troutman drops 28 as Ohio cruises past Samford
article.linkText: Troutman drops 28 as Ohio cruises past Samford
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Sonny Troutman matched his career high with 28 points Saturday night, leading Ohio to a 64-52 victory over Samford. Ohio (15-8) pulled ahead 7-6 and never trailed again, extending its lead to 15 points midway through the second half. Leon Williams added 17 points and 11 rebounds, his sixth double-double of the season. Mychal Green, who was shooting only 24 percent from the field in his last six games, broke out of his slump by going 6-of-10 for 14 points. Samford (17-9) got 13 points from Randall Gulina and 11 from Joe Ross Merritt. Samford got only three free throws in the game, and missed all of them. Ohio closed the first half with a 9-4 flurry that started with a 3-pointer and a jumper by Green. The Bobcats then stretched their 31-24 halftime advantage into a 15-point lead midway through the second half. Samford never got closer than eight points the rest of the way.
